The 2021 ARC calendar will have six rounds spread across the African continent. Rwanda will open the ARC calendar in March while South Africa will close the series in November.The complete 2021 ARC Calendar: Rwanda 20-21 March, Kenya 24-25 April, Tanzania 24-25 July, Uganda 21-22 August, Zambia 25-26 September, South Africa 6-7 November. The Rift Valley Motor Sports Club (RVMSC) of Nakuru will kick off the 2021 Kenya National Rally Championship (KNRC) season with its opening event on 20-21 February.
The newly released calendar will rely heavily on the coronavirus situation, which has messed up many of the competitions this season not only in Kenya but across the globe.



