There will be two major events in the form of the Equator Rally of the African Rally Championship (ARC) series, followed by the main World Rally Championship (WRC) Safari Rally in June.
KNRC calendar 2021:  RVMSC (Nakuru) 20-21 February, Kenya Motor Sports Club (Nairobi) 27-28 March, Equator Rally (Nairobi) 24-25 April,  Western Kenya Motor Club (Eldoret) 5-6 June, Mombasa Motor Club (Mombasa) July31 -1 August, Nanyuki Rally Group (Nanyuki) 4-5 September, Rallye Sports Club (Nairobi) 16-17 October, and Simba Union Club (Nairobi) 4-5 December.





***
The 2021 ARC calendar will have six rounds spread across the African continent. Rwanda will open the ARC calendar in March while South Africa will close the series in November.
The complete 2021 ARC Calendar: Rwanda 20-21 March, Kenya 24-25 April, Tanzania 24-25 July, Uganda 21-22 August, Zambia 25-26 September, South Africa 6-7 November.
 ***
Three more clubs have been affiliated to the Kenya Motor Sports Federation (KMSF). The total number of clubs across the country is now 15.  Delta Motor Sports Club, Kenya Racing Team and Meru Motor Sports Club have become the latest clubs to fall under the national motor sports governing body.
For any club to organise an event in Kenya, the KMSF has to be notified in advance for the competition to be officially cleared.



