KMSF clubs shall at all times refrain from manifesting racial, political or religious discrimination in the course of administering motorsport actives in Kenya.
Among other objectives, KMSF has to promote the development of motor sport, improve on safety in motor sport, enact, interpret and enforce common rules applicable to the FIA Code of Conduct.
***
Among the new events in the coming season include training, National Drifting Championship, Kenya National Drag Racing Championship, and the Time Trials and the 4X4 Championship which will be run off-road in the “Rhino Charge’ format, among others.
***
Did you know that….
Kenya’s Equator Rally will make its long-awaited comeback to the 2021 FIA ARC series on April 24-25, according to the 2021 motorsport calendar released Wednesday.
